        <div class="note">
            <p class="Note-Text" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #fdc80b;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">You can generate a report to see places in your project where you might want to create a cross-reference. Essentially, Flare finds files where a hyperlink to a topic exists. Because cross-references are generally preferred over hyperlinks (due to the fact that they are dynamic), it suggests that you create a cross-reference instead.    <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Flare/Analysis/Reports/Reports.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Reports</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Flare/Analysis/Reports/Generating-Reports.htm" target="" title="" alt="">Generating Reports</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
